&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly motivated and detail-oriented Software Quality Analyst with a strong passion for ensuring the delivery of high-quality software products. As a Software Quality Analyst, you will play a critical role in the software development process by conducting thorough manual testing to identify defects and verify that the software meets established quality standards. You will collaborate closely with cross-functional teams, including developers, PMs, automation engineers, and other stakeholders, to ensure a smooth and efficient testing process.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with software development teams at BBPOS (Hong Kong) and Stripe Terminal (US) to identify project requirements, specifications and acceptance criteria for products such as SDKs, iOS and Android Apps, Firmware and Service products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop comprehensive test plans and test cases to validate software functionality and meet user requirements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform functional, regression and user acceptance testing to identify defects and verify stability and accuracy of software products before releasing to users.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct EMV Certification testing on different Credit Card brands, like VISA, Mastercard, China Union Pay on BBPOS terminal readers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report software defects and work closely with developers and project managers to ensure resolution of identified defects and monitor resolution process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide timely updates on testing progress and results to project stakeholders including potential risks and impact on users.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously refine the testing process by identifying opportunities for efficiency improvements and test automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
