&lt;p&gt;Initially, a large part of your focus will be on defining, coordinating, and executing the Terminal release management process. Those responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate across several teams (engineering, product, go-to-market, docs, design etc.) and domains to finalize, bundle, and release software changes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work intimately with app, SDK, and API services teams to release new API versions, SDKs for each supported language, and other software assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the safe rollout of updated software assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with the Terminal team to update product documentation &amp;amp; integration guides, API references, migration guides, and changelogs as appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the product development team responsible for a given release to communicate changes effectively to existing and prospective users&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
